  "description": "Beancount is a plain-text, double-entry accounting system written in Python, created by Martin Blais [citation needed]. Like Ledger, transactions are stored in human-readable text files.\n¶What It Does Beancount reads plain-text input files containing transactions, account declarations, and balance assertions, then produces reports and financial statements. It includes Fava, a web-based UI for viewing reports and navigating the ledger — making it more accessible than pure command-line tools while keeping the plain-text data model.\n",
